Many if the units of capacity (or liquid volume in US English) have the same names, but have different volumes and in the case of fluid ounces and pints, different relations. In addition the definitions of the imperial and US gallons are based on different concepts<U+2014>the imperial gallon is defined in terms of the volume occupied by a specified mass of water while the US gallon is specified in terms of a volume.

