====Apothecaries Weight====
{{main|Apothecaries' system}}
Apothecaries weights were used in the [[Pharmacy|pharmaceutical]] industry and have remained almost unchanged since the Middle Ages <U+2013> the Apothecaries pound and ounce being the same as the Troy pound and ounce, but each system having different sub-units. In the United Kingdom, these units are of historic interest only, having been replaced by metric units in 1970.<ref>{{cite book
|title = Dictionary of Weights, Measures and Units
|first1 = Donald
|last1 = Fenna
|publisher = [[Oxford University Press]]
|at = apothecaries scale
|isbn = 0-19-860522-6
|year = 2002}}</ref>

